<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1957,2020]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1437,151,789]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="572" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">
However, although 
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius, C." box="[372,577,1957,1983]" pageId="2" pageNumber="571" pagination="361 - 403" refId="ref7867" refString="Aurivillius, C. (1920) Neue oder wenig bekannte Coleoptera Longicornia. 17. Arkiv for Zoologi, 13 (9), 361 - 403. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 20147" type="journal article" year="1920">Aurivillius (1920)</bibRefCitation>
did not indicate the color of the scape, it is possible to see that it is reddish brown with the apex blackish in a 
<typeStatus box="[541,628,1994,2020]" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">syntype</typeStatus>
male (
<figureCitation box="[706,776,1993,2019]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1883,1907]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,181,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[151,1436,181,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Cobelura spp. 9–10) Cobelura peruviana (Aurivillius, 1920), male: 9) Syntype (by Jesus Santiago Moure); 10) Specimen from Monné (1984). 11–14) Cobelura vermicularis Kirsch, 1889, female holotype: 11) Labels; 12) Dorsal habitus; 13) Ventral habitus; 14) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612813" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4612813/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="571">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
). It is true that there are no distinct longitudinal pubescent bands on pronotum of the male 
<typeStatus box="[510,597,151,177]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[635,782,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[635,782,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as that the elytra are entirely black. Nevertheless, it is possible that these features are variable in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[672,819,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[672,819,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as for example, the color of the femora, which may be dark or entirely reddish (
<bibRefCitation author="Aurivillius, C." box="[428,618,223,249]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" pagination="361 - 403" refId="ref7867" refString="Aurivillius, C. (1920) Neue oder wenig bekannte Coleoptera Longicornia. 17. Arkiv for Zoologi, 13 (9), 361 - 403. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 20147" type="journal article" year="1920">Aurivillius 1920</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">
Still according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Corbett, D. C." box="[399,565,259,285]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" pagination="277 - 280" refId="ref8298" refString="Corbett, D. C. (2004) Sinopse do genero Cobelura (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Acanthocinini), com descric &quot; o de tres especies novas. Iheringia, Zoologia, 94 (3), 277 - 280. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0073 - 47212004000300009" type="journal article" year="2004">Corbett (2004)</bibRefCitation>
(translated from Portuguese): “ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Devesa" authorityYear="2021" box="[919,1144,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stockwelli">
<emphasis box="[919,1144,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">Cobelura stockwelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[1290,1437,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[1290,1437,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirsch" authorityYear="1889" box="[200,375,295,321]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vermicularis">
<emphasis box="[200,375,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. vermicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the pronotum and elytra with abundant small yellowish-white pubescent maculae, without whitish or brownish pubescent band … However, the maculae in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Devesa" authorityYear="2021" box="[880,1025,331,357]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stockwelli">
<emphasis box="[880,1025,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. stockwelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are larger and irregular, more or less confluent in two longitudinal bands on pronotum, and may be agglomerated or even fused on the lateral of the elytra (on median region or apical third) … In 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[602,749,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[602,749,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kirsch" authorityYear="1889" box="[803,978,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vermicularis">
<emphasis box="[803,978,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. vermicularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: maculae very small, well-distributed on pronotum and elytral surface.” There is no difference between the size of the pubescent maculae in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[1288,1437,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[1288,1437,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<typeStatus box="[159,249,475,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">syntype</typeStatus>
) and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Devesa" authorityYear="2021" box="[312,458,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stockwelli">
<emphasis box="[312,458,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. stockwelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As 
<bibRefCitation author="Corbett, D. C." box="[509,676,475,501]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" pagination="277 - 280" refId="ref8298" refString="Corbett, D. C. (2004) Sinopse do genero Cobelura (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Acanthocinini), com descric &quot; o de tres especies novas. Iheringia, Zoologia, 94 (3), 277 - 280. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0073 - 47212004000300009" type="journal article" year="2004">Corbett (2004)</bibRefCitation>
affirmed that the pubescent maculae on elytra of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Devesa" authorityYear="2021" box="[1235,1381,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stockwelli">
<emphasis box="[1235,1381,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. stockwelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be agglomerated or even fused on the lateral of the elytra, we can conclude that they may be as in the 
<typeStatus box="[1286,1373,511,537]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1920" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In this case, the differences between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Devesa" authorityYear="2021" box="[689,834,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stockwelli">
<emphasis box="[689,834,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. stockwelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[888,1034,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[888,1034,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
become questionable. For now, it is not possible to affirm that they are or not the same species without examining a large number of specimens.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,151,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A." box="[352,513,619,645]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" pagination="337 - 344" refId="ref8848" refString="Monne, M. A. (1984) Revis &quot; o do genero Cobelura Erichson, 1847 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Acanthocinini). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 28 (3), 337 - 344." type="journal article" year="1984">Monné (1984)</bibRefCitation>
(translated from Portuguese): “Antennae just surpass elytral apex.” However, they distinctly surpass the elytral apex in the 
<typeStatus box="[607,694,655,681]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">syntype</typeStatus>
male, and also in the male specimen illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A." box="[1274,1436,655,681]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" pagination="337 - 344" refId="ref8848" refString="Monne, M. A. (1984) Revis &quot; o do genero Cobelura Erichson, 1847 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Acanthocinini). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 28 (3), 337 - 344." type="journal article" year="1984">Monné (1984)</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[160,243,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1883,1907]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,181,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[151,1436,181,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Cobelura spp. 9–10) Cobelura peruviana (Aurivillius, 1920), male: 9) Syntype (by Jesus Santiago Moure); 10) Specimen from Monné (1984). 11–14) Cobelura vermicularis Kirsch, 1889, female holotype: 11) Labels; 12) Dorsal habitus; 13) Ventral habitus; 14) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612813" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4612813/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
). According to the key from 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. &amp; Monne, M. A." box="[564,842,691,717]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" pagination="253 - 262" refId="ref9239" refString="Monne, M. L &amp; Monne, M. A. (2017) New species of Neotropical Acanthocinini (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae). Zootaxa, 4299 (2), 253 - 262. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4299.2.5" type="journal article" year="2017">Monné &amp; Monné (2017)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Santos-Silva &amp; Devesa" authorityYear="2021" box="[854,998,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="stockwelli">
<emphasis box="[854,998,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. stockwelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[1145,1292,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[1145,1292,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the scape black only apically in the former, and entirely black in the latter. This information does not agree with the 
<typeStatus box="[1349,1436,727,753]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Aurivillius" baseAuthorityYear="1920" box="[182,328,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Cobelura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis box="[182,328,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">C. peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[343,410,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1883,1907]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,181,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[151,1436,181,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Cobelura spp. 9–10) Cobelura peruviana (Aurivillius, 1920), male: 9) Syntype (by Jesus Santiago Moure); 10) Specimen from Monné (1984). 11–14) Cobelura vermicularis Kirsch, 1889, female holotype: 11) Labels; 12) Dorsal habitus; 13) Ventral habitus; 14) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612813" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4612813/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) and, apparently, nor with the specimen illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Monne, M. A." box="[1020,1180,763,789]" pageId="3" pageNumber="572" pagination="337 - 344" refId="ref8848" refString="Monne, M. A. (1984) Revis &quot; o do genero Cobelura Erichson, 1847 (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae, Lamiinae, Acanthocinini). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 28 (3), 337 - 344." type="journal article" year="1984">Monné (1984)</bibRefCitation>
(
<figureCitation box="[1196,1279,763,789]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–14" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1883,1907]" captionTargetBox="[159,1424,181,1854]" captionTargetId="figure-21@5.[151,1436,181,1860]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 9–14. Cobelura spp. 9–10) Cobelura peruviana (Aurivillius, 1920), male: 9) Syntype (by Jesus Santiago Moure); 10) Specimen from Monné (1984). 11–14) Cobelura vermicularis Kirsch, 1889, female holotype: 11) Labels; 12) Dorsal habitus; 13) Ventral habitus; 14) Lateral habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4612813" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4612813/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="572">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
